    {
      "number": 3,
      "title": "能愿动词「得」— Modal Verb dei (must / have to)",
      "explanation": "得(děi) is a modal verb meaning 'must' or 'have to'. It expresses obligation or necessity. Formula: Subject + 得 + Verb. Negation: 不用(bú yòng, don't need to) or 不能(bù néng, cannot) — NOT 不得(which has a different meaning). Example: 你得多休息。(You have to rest more.) 我现在得回家。(I have to go home now.)",
